<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include("partials/head.ejs") %>
<body>
<div class="page">
    <header>
        <div class="logo">
            <div class="logo-icon" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div>
                <div class="logo-title">Gazetionnaire</div>
                <div class="logo-sub">Gaze-controlled questionnaires</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tagline">
            Designed for people with motor impairments ‚ôø
        </div>
    </header>

    <main>
        <!-- HERO -->
        <section class="hero">
            <div>
                <div class="hero-highlight">
                    <span>Hands-free answering</span> ¬∑ <span>Webcam only</span>
                </div>
                <h1 class="hero-title">
                    The first <span>gaze-controlled questionnaire</span> on the web.
                </h1>
                <p class="hero-subtitle">
                    Gazetionnaire lets participants answer surveys using only their eyes.
                    No mouse, no keyboard‚Äîjust gaze, dwell-time and gentle gaze gestures.
                </p>

                <div class="hero-buttons">
                    <button class="btn-primary">
                        ‚ñ∂ Try demo question
                    </button>
                    <button class="btn-ghost">
                        üë©‚Äçüî¨ For researchers & clinicians
                    </button>
                </div>
                <div class="hero-meta">
                    Works in modern browsers ¬∑ Uses webcam eye-tracking (e.g. GazeCloudAPI) ¬∑
                    Ideal for accessibility studies, HCI research and remote testing.
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Visual preview card -->
            <div class="hero-card" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="hero-card-header">
                    <span>Live gaze preview</span>
                    <span class="hero-chip">Dwell-time selection ¬∑ 1.2s</span>
                </div>

                <div class="question-card">
                    <div class="question-label">Question 3 ¬∑ Likert scale</div>
                    <p class="question-text">
                        How easy was it to answer this question <strong>using only your eyes</strong>?
                    </p>

                    <div class="options">
                        <div class="option">
                            <div class="option-dot"></div>
                            Strongly disagree
                        </div>
                        <div class="option">
                            <div class="option-dot"></div>
                            Disagree
                        </div>
                        <div class="option is-target">
                            <div class="option-dot"></div>
                            Neutral
                            <div class="gaze-ring"></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="option">
                            <div class="option-dot"></div>
                            Agree
                        </div>
                        <div class="option">
                            <div class="option-dot"></div>
                            Strongly agree
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="dwell-bar">
                        <div class="dwell-bar-inner"></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="dwell-label">
                        <span>Gaze locked on ‚ÄúNeutral‚Äù</span>
                        <span>Selection in 0.4 s</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- FEATURES -->
        <section class="section">
            <h2>Built for accessibility, powered by eye-tracking.</h2>
            <p>
                Gazetionnaire combines webcam-based eye-tracking with carefully designed
                questionnaires. You can mix multiple choice, Likert scales, yes/no questions
                and even an on-screen keyboard controlled purely by gaze.
            </p>

            <div class="feature-grid">
                <article class="feature-card">
                    <div class="feature-label">Selection methods</div>
                    <div class="feature-title">Dwell-time, smooth pursuit &amp; gaze gestures</div>
                    <div class="feature-body">
                        Compare three gaze-interaction techniques in one interface and log
                        detailed metrics for each.
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article class="feature-card">
                    <div class="feature-label">Question types</div>
                    <div class="feature-title">Flexible questionnaire system</div>
                    <div class="feature-body">
                        Multiple choice, Likert scales, yes/no, and short text via on-screen keyboard ‚Äì
                        all controllable with eye movements.
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article class="feature-card">
                    <div class="feature-label">Participants</div>
                    <div class="feature-title">For motor-impaired &amp; able-bodied users</div>
                    <div class="feature-body">
                        Run studies with restrained-hands simulations and real users with motor impairments.
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article class="feature-card">
                    <div class="feature-label">Analytics</div>
                    <div class="feature-title">Per-option gaze statistics</div>
                    <div class="feature-body">
                        Track how long each answer is looked at, how often users switch, and which
                        selection method feels most natural.
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article class="feature-card">
                    <div class="feature-label">Web-based</div>
                    <div class="feature-title">No installation needed</div>
                    <div class="feature-body">
                        Just send a link. Participants use their own webcam and browser ‚Äì ideal for
                        remote experiments.
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article class="feature-card">
                    <div class="feature-label">Tech stack</div>
                    <div class="feature-title">JavaScript + Eye-Tracking API</div>
                    <div class="feature-body">
                        Integrates with libraries like GazeCloudAPI and custom models. Your logic
                        runs entirely in the browser.
                    </div>
                </article>
            </div>

            <div class="badge-row">
                <span class="badge badge-soft">Prototype in progress</span>
                <span class="badge">Ideal for Bachelor / Master thesis</span>
                <span class="badge">HCI ¬∑ Accessibility ¬∑ Assistive Tech</span>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
        <section class="section">
            <h2>How it works (for participants)</h2>
            <p>
                Gazetionnaire keeps the setup simple so that participants can focus on the questions,
                not the technology.
            </p>

            <div class="steps">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-num">1</div>
                    <strong>Give camera permission</strong><br>
                    The browser asks for webcam access. Only the gaze data stays in the session;
                    no video is stored.
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-num">2</div>
                    <strong>Quick gaze calibration</strong><br>
                    Users follow a few points on the screen. The system learns how their eyes map
                    to screen coordinates.
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-num">3</div>
                    <strong>Answer questions with your eyes</strong><br>
                    Look at an option to highlight it. Keep your gaze to select (dwell),
                    or confirm with a simple gaze gesture.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <span>¬© 2025 Gazetionnaire ¬∑ Prototype</span>
        <span>Made for inclusive, gaze-first interaction on the web.</span>
    </footer>
</div>
</body>
</html>
